text: Theodore Gosewisch House, also known as Fuenfhausen Residence, is a historic home located near Lexington, Lafayette County, Missouri. It was built about 1847, and is a two-story, central passage plan, Greek Revival style brick I-house. It has a two-story rear ell with open shed-roofed porch. The front facade features a one-story Victorian front porch installed in the early 1900s. (includes 15 photographs from 1996) It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1997. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Greek Revival houses in Missouri Category:Victorian architecture in Missouri Category:Houses completed in 1847 Category:Houses in Lafayette County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Lafayette County, Missouri
